&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clinical Fellow in Haemophilia and Thrombosis&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Haemophilia, Haemostasis &amp; Thrombosis Centre at Hampshire Hospital NHS Foundation Trust is seeking to appoint a Clinical Fellow to join a dynamic, enthusiastic and forward thinking team. We are looking to appoint an individual with appropriate skills to complement this team and keep the service in the forefront of clinical and academic excellence. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will compromise both clinical duties as well as involvement in various research projects that the department is delivering. The Centre has an established portfolio of research studies including commercial and NIHR Portfolio trials. There may be the opportunity to participate in the on call rota covering both general and haemostasis, depending on the candidates experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be fully registered with the GMC and hold License to Practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is offered on a fixed term contract, up to 12 months, with a 5 days per week commitment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDr Sarah ManglesJob titleClinical Director Haemophilia and ThrombosisEmail addresssarah.mangles@hhft.nhs.ukTelephone number01256 314793&lt;/p&gt;
